    <p>The anti-inflammatory effects may calm redness. Start with low concentration.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<p>Always patch test before full-face application. Stop use if irritation develops and consult your dermatologist.</p>

<hr class="sep"/>

<h2>Hair Growth Applications</h2>

<p>GHK-Cu shows significant promise for hair restoration. It works differently from common hair growth treatments.</p>

<p>Instead of just stimulating growth, it targets the hair follicle environment. This makes it effective for various hair loss types.</p>

<h3>How GHK-Cu Supports Hair Health</h3>

<p>GHK-Cu works through multiple mechanisms to support hair follicles:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Follicle enlargement</strong>: Increases the size of miniaturized follicles</li>
  <li><strong>Blood vessel formation</strong>: Promotes angiogenesis around follicles</li>
  <li><strong>DHT protection</strong>: May help protect follicles from hormone-related damage</li>
  <li><strong>Stem cell activation</strong>: Wakes up dormant hair follicles</li>
  <li><strong>Scalp health</strong>: Reduces inflammation that contributes to hair loss</li>
</ul>

<p>This multi-target approach makes it unique among hair growth treatments. It does not just stimulate hair, it creates a healthier scalp environment.</p>

<div class="d d-p">
  <div class="s">Trichologist Perspective</div>
  <p>What sets GHK-Cu apart is its ability to rebuild the hair follicle's support structure. It does not just grow hair, it creates a healthier environment for long-term hair maintenance. I have seen it work where other treatments failed.</p>
</div>

<h3>Hair Growth Treatment Comparison</h3>

<table class="tbl">
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Treatment</th><th>Primary Action</th><th>Results</th><th>Maintenance</th><th>Side Effects</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><strong>GHK-Cu</strong></td><td>Follicle restoration</td><td>3-6 months</td><td>Ongoing use</td><td class="g">Mild scalp tingling</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Minoxidil</td><td>Blood flow increase</td><td>4-6 months</td><td>Continuous use</td><td class="y">Scalp irritation, unwanted facial hair</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Finasteride</td><td>Hormone blocking</td><td>6-12 months</td><td>Continuous use</td><td class="r">Sexual side effects, not for women</td></tr>
    <tr><td>PRP Therapy</td><td>Growth factor stimulation</td><td>3-4 months</td><td>Repeat sessions</td><td class="y">Pain, bruising, high cost</td></tr>
