</details>

<details>
  <summary>Can I use GHK-Cu with other active ingredients?</summary>
  <div class="fa">Yes, but introduce new products gradually. It pairs well with hyaluronic acid, vitamin C, and niacinamide. Avoid combining with strong acids or retinoids initially as this may increase irritation risk. Consult your dermatologist about combinations.</div>
</details>

<details>
  <summary>Why does my GHK-Cu serum turn blue?</summary>
  <div class="fa">Some formulations develop a blue tint as the copper oxidizes. This does not necessarily mean the product has gone bad, but it may indicate reduced potency. Store in cool, dark places to slow oxidation. If the color changes dramatically, consider replacing it.</div>
</details>

<details>
  <summary>How long do results last after stopping?</summary>
  <div class="fa">Benefits gradually diminish over 4-8 weeks after discontinuation. Like most skin and hair treatments, ongoing use is needed to maintain results. Think of it like exercise for your skin: consistency brings lasting benefits.</div>
</details>

<details>
  <summary>Is GHK-Cu effective for eyebrow and eyelash growth?</summary>
  <div class="fa">Yes, but use extreme caution near eyes. Apply with a cotton swab and avoid direct contact with eyes. Consider specially formulated products for these delicate areas. Never apply to the lash line where it could enter the eye.</div>
</details>

<details>
  <summary>Can men and women both use GHK-Cu?</summary>
  <div class="fa">Absolutely. The mechanisms work similarly regardless of gender. Both men and women see benefits for skin rejuvenation and hair support. Women may prefer lower concentrations initially if they have sensitive skin.</div>
</details>

<details>
  <summary>Does sun exposure affect GHK-Cu?</summary>
  <div class="fa">UV light can degrade the peptide. Apply in the evening or use sunscreen during the day. Some evidence suggests GHK-Cu may actually enhance sun protection when used with sunscreen. Consider it part of your UV defense strategy.</div>
</details>

<details>
  <summary>Are there oral forms of GHK-Cu?</summary>
  <div class="fa">While some companies offer oral supplements, research primarily supports topical application. The peptide may not survive digestion intact to reach target tissues. Topical application delivers it directly where it is needed most.</div>
</details>

<details>
  <summary>Can I use GHK-Cu on my body?</summary>
  <div class="fa">Yes, it is effective for improving skin texture on the neck, chest, and hands. These areas show aging similar to the face. Use the same application techniques as for facial skin.</div>
</details>

<details>
  <summary>How does GHK-Cu compare to retinoids?</summary>
  <div class="fa">GHK-Cu works through different mechanisms than retinoids. It is generally better tolerated with less irritation. However, retinoids remain the gold standard for collagen stimulation. Many dermatologists recommend using both at different times.</div>
</details>

</div>

